# Cover Design Rules

Guide: `01_artist/cover_design_guide.md`  
Command: `/cover prompt` in `00_system/commands.md`

## Principles

Each cover has **its own identity** — read album `visual_direction.md`; don't clone one layout onto another.

Optional visual anchor (sun, horizon, figure) — define per album in visual direction.

## Families (pick one)

| Family | Template | Best for |
|--------|----------|----------|
| Nature / trust | `cover_prompt_nature_trust.md` | Gentle, hopeful, child-safe |
| Single photo | `cover_prompt_single_photo.md` | Singles, live moment |
| Custom | `cover_prompt_template.md` | Build from scratch |

Master structure: `04_templates/cover_prompt_template.md`.

## Workflow

1. Read album `visual_direction.md` + `album_art/visual_direction.md` + `cover_notes.md`.
2. Write `album_art/cover_prompt_vN.md` (new version, don't overwrite).
3. Output copy-paste **Image prompt** + **Negative prompt** — usually **no text in image gen** (type in post).
4. Final chosen cover → `cover.png`; document why in `cover_notes.md`.

## Avoid on all covers

Religious iconography, stock wellness clichés, glossy pop, neon/cyber, random concept art that doesn't match the album's story.
